changes.name: CHANGE_1
changes.summary:
Update screening language: 
Edit the rescreening language
changes.rationale: To allow for the repeat of screening assessments within the screening window or to allow a subject to rescreen once for the study. Due to the nature of the participant population and the study design, subject safety and data integrity will not be impacted

changes.name: CHANGE_2
changes.summary:
Clarify inclusion and exclusion criteria: 
Move exclusion criterion 18 to the inclusion criteria and clarify the CYP450 enzymes that are excluded for exclusion criterion 19.
changes.rationale: Previous exclusion 18 should be answered affirmatively in order for the subject to be eligible for participation; as a result, this exclusion should be listed as an inclusion. Exclusion 19 excluded all inducers of metabolism; however, after consideration, it is only necessary to exclude inducers of CYP3A4.

changes.name: CHANGE_3
changes.summary:
Clarify procedure for continuous end tidal CO2:
Add clarification that subjects may remove cannula to dose or eat
changes.rationale: The timepoints overlap for the collection of end tidal CO2 and it would not be possible for the subject to dose or eat with the cannula in place.

changes.name: CHANGE_4
changes.summary:
Lower the respiratory rate alarm for continuous end tidal CO2 alarms: 
The alarm for respiratory rate low was 10 bpm and is now 6 bpm.
changes.rationale: Generally, respiratory rates between 6 and 10 are not clinically relevant. A low respiratory rate alarm of 6 will allow a more accurate clinical determination of a true signal.

changes.name: CHANGE_5
changes.summary:
Edit Spot CO2 respiratory rate values: 
The spot values are lowered to start at > 24, and continue with increments of 4 bpm: >28, >32, and >36.
changes.rationale: This change is made to align with the protocol, Table 7, alarm values.

titles.text: A Phase 1 Randomized, Placebo-controlled Study to Assess the Safety, Tolerability and Pharmacokinetics of Multiple Doses of ASP8062 with a Single Dose of Morphine in Recreational Opioid Using Participants

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I1
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 1
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC)-approved written informed consent and privacy language as per national regulations (e.g., Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act authorization for US sites) must be obtained from the participant prior to any study-related procedures (including withdrawal of prohibited medication, if applicable).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I2
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 2
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant is a male or female participant between 18 to 60 years of age, inclusive at screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I3
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 3
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant is a recreational opioid user who has used opioids for nontherapeutic (recreational) purposes on at least 10 occasions within their lifetime, with at least 1 opioid use in the last 90 days.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I4
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 4
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a body mass index (BMI) range of 18 to 36 kg/m2 , inclusive and weighs at least 50 kg at screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I5
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 5
eligibilityCriterionItems.text:
Female participant is not pregnant (see [Section 10.2 Appendix 2 Contraception Requirements]) and at least 1 of the following conditions apply:
  • Not a woman of childbearing potential (WOCBP) (see [Section 10.2 Appendix 2 Contraception Requirements])
  • WOCBP who agrees to follow the contraceptive guidance (see [Section 10.2 Appendix 2 Contraception Requirements]) from the time of informed consent through at least 28 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I6
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 6
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Female participant must agree not to breastfeed starting at screening and throughout the study period and for 28 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I7
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 7
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Female participant must not donate ova starting at first dose of IP and throughout the study period and for 28 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I8
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 8
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male participant with female partner(s) of childbearing potential (including breastfeeding partner[s]) must agree to use contraception (see [Section 10.2 Appendix 2 Contraception Requirements]), throughout the treatment period and for 90 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I9
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 9
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male participant must not donate sperm during the treatment period and for 90 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I10
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 10
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male participant with a pregnant partner(s) must agree to remain abstinent or use a condom with spermicide for the duration of the pregnancy throughout the study period and for 90 days after final IP administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I11
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 11
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant agrees to not participate in another interventional study while participating in the present study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: INC-I12
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Inclusion item 12
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant must be willing to abstain from smoking (including use of tobacco-containing products and nicotine or nicotine-containing products [e.g., electronic vapes]) from at least 1 hour predose through at least 8 hours postdose on days 9 and 10.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I1
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 1
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has received any investigational therapy within 28 days or 5 half-lives, whichever is longer, prior to screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I2
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 2
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has any condition which, in an investigator's opinion, makes the participant unsuitable for study participation.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I3
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 3
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Female participant who has been pregnant within 6 months prior to screening or breastfeeding within 3 months prior to screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I4
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 4
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a known or suspected hypersensitivity to ASP8062 or morphine and/or other opioids, or any components of the formulations used.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I5
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 5
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has had previous exposure with ASP8062.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I6
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 6
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has any of the liver function tests (alkaline phosphatase [ALP], alanine aminotransferase [ALT], aspartate aminotransferase [AST], gamma-glutamyl transferase and total bilirubin [TBL]) ≥ 1.5 × upper limit of normal (ULN) on day -1. In such a case, the assessment may be repeated once.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I7
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 7
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has any clinically significant history of allergic conditions (including drug allergies, asthma or anaphylactic reactions, but excluding untreated, asymptomatic, seasonal allergies) prior to first IP administration as judged by an investigator.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I8
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 8
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has any history or evidence of any clinically significant cardiovascular, gastrointestinal, endocrinologic, hematologic, hepatic, immunologic, metabolic, urologic, pulmonary, neurologic, dermatologic, renal and/or other major disease or malignancy, as judged by an investigator, with exception of history of cholecystectomy.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I9
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 9
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a history of moderate or severe use disorder for any substance other than caffeine or tobacco (based on the DSM-5 criteria).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I10
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 10
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a history or presence of any clinically significant psychiatric disorders such as, bipolar 1, schizophrenia, schizoaffective disorder or major depressive disorders, as judged by an investigator.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I11
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 11
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has had recent suicidal ideation within the last 12 months or participant who is at significant risk to commit suicide, as judged by an investigator, using the Baseline/Screening Columbia-suicide severity rating scale (C-SSRS) at screening and the Since Last Visit C-SSRS on day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I12
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 12
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has/had febrile illness or symptomatic, viral, bacterial (including upper respiratory infection) or fungal (noncutaneous) infection within 1 week prior to day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I13
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 13
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has any clinically significant abnormality following an investigator's review of the physical examination, ECG and protocol-defined clinical laboratory tests at screening or on day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I14
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 14
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a mean pulse < 50 or > 90 bpm; mean systolic blood pressure > 150 mmHg; mean diastolic blood pressure > 95 mmHg (measurements taken in duplicate after participant has been resting in the supine position for at least 5 minutes) on day -1. If the mean blood pressure exceeds the limits above, 1 additional duplicate may be taken.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I15
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 15
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a mean corrected QT interval using Fridericia's formula (QTcF) of > 450 msec (for male participants) and > 470 msec (for female participants) on day -1. If the mean QTcF exceeds the limits above, 1 additional triplicate ECG may be taken.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I16
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 16
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a positive test for amphetamines, barbiturates, benzodiazepines, cocaine, phencyclidine, alcohol and/or opiates on day -1. Positive tetrahydrocannabinol is not exclusionary and a cannabis intoxication evaluation will be performed. Participant may be reconsidered at an investigator's discretion.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I17
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 17
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has used any prescribed or nonprescribed drugs (including vitamins and natural and herbal remedies, e.g., St. John's Wort) in the 2 weeks prior to first IP administration, except for occasional use of acetaminophen (up to 2 g/day), topical dermatological products, including corticosteroid products, hormonal contraceptives and hormone replacement therapy (HRT).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I18
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 18
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has used any inducer of CYP3A4-related metabolism (e.g., barbiturates, rifampin, apalutamide, carbamazepine, enzalutamide, mitotane, phenytoin, St. John's wort, bosentan, efavirenz, etravirine, phenobarbital, primidone, armodafinil, modafinil, and rufinamide) in the 3 months prior to day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I19
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 19
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has had significant blood loss, donated approximately 500 mL of whole blood (excluding plasma donation) within 56 days prior to screening or donated plasma within 7 days prior to day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I20
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 20
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has a positive serology test for hepatitis B surface antigen, hepatitis C virus antibodies or antibodies to HIV type 1 and/or type 2 at screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I21
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 21
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant has loss of ability to freely provide consent through imprisonment or involuntary incarceration for treatment of either a psychiatric or physical (e.g., infectious disease) illness.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: EXC-I22
eligibilityCriterionItems.label: Exclusion item 22
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participant is an employee of Astellas, the study-related contract research organizations (CROs) or the clinical unit.
